<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14498] Audit log does not include statements on some system keyspaces</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14498</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Audit logs does not include statements on the &quot;system&quot; and &quot;system_schema&quot; keyspace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It may be a common use case to whitelist queries on these keyspaces, but Cassandra should not make assumptions. Users who don&apos;t want these statements in their audit log are still able to whitelist them with configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13164206">CASSANDRA-14498</key>
            <summary>Audit log does not include statements on some system keyspaces</summary>
